	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    A Magician Guide from a level 23</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:XeniXTTRW@hotmail.com">Dolelen Celestine of The Rathe</a> | 
		            6/25/1999 2:42:38 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">First of all, I want you all to know, that No matter what anyone tells you, you cannot JUST wear cloth. One of the other guides on here says that, and i feel i had to clear that up. Also, i don't think Guides should be made by people under level 15. Now for the stuff y'all have been waiting for.<BR>
<BR>
Magician Guide:<BR>
Level 1-4: First off, Find your guild. Hand your master your note, and Wield your robe. Then, equip your dagger, Scribe and Memorize your spells, and head out to the newbie area. At level 1 kill snakes. Level 2 kill Rats, Snakes, and Fire beetles. Level 3 kill black bears in a group with some friends, and finally, at level 4, we reach the Mages Highest Strength. ELEMENTALS!!! You can choose 4 types of elementals (Air, Water, Fire, Earth) but Earth would be your best bet for a level 4 character. <BR>
5-8: Head out to your Low level (but not kiddie pool) zone. If you're in freeport or Neriak, i recommend the East Commonlands. Qeynos Area, I would use the West Karanas (Qeynos hills). At 5, solo Bears with your pet, and kill Pumas (if an option). Do this til about level 7, but ALWAYS ALWAYS ALWAYS kill things that are black. At level 7, bust up some Giant spiders and Young Kodiaks in groups. Finally, after a greuling level 7, we reach a new spell circle: Level 8. If you don't have the money for all the spells, just get an Earth pet and Shock of Blades. Flame Bolt can come later (it frequently misses, and shock of blades does about the same damage using less mana). <BR>
<BR>
Levels 8-12: At 8, go to the Desert of Ro (best place, sorry Erudites.), and kill Desert Tarantulas and Sand Scarabs in groups and keep getting in smaller and smaller groups until level 10. At level 10, Kill Darkweed Snakes, letting your pet take the hits (elementals have HIGH resistance to poison, and it doesn't drain their life.). You can take Darkweeds all the way to level 12 or 13 your choice. But at level 12, be sure you get an AIR pet, and Bind affinity (radius spells are optional, I don't really like em, don't use em much). Hopefully you know what bind affinity does. <BR>
<BR>
Here's the last section. (im gonna let you do it on your own now) By now i hope you have a Runed Totem Staff and at least a Sr. Apprentice Robe. at level 12 take your pet down to Befallen, and camp Skeleton Lrodd in his chamber. He gives Mad EXP for the Ease of killing him, but it takes a little while, and camping him does get a bit old. If you're ever bored at level 12, just have a high level help you at the east commonlands Ruins to take one ghoul while you kill the other. They're a relatively hard battle, and they give badass loot :). <BR>
<BR>
Thank you for reading my guide. Good Luck to yaz 
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>
