im only 16 now and my account has stopped for the time being until i can start it up again but what i did was hunt in newbie area ( all of this is gunna take place around freeport area so if ur not there try to get a port its the best place for lvling.)until lvl 3. then i went to the ec and fought anything from wolfs to fire beetles to spiderlings. as soon as i became 6 i immediatly started looking for and orc group (i might have started at 5 but usualy thats too low). that got me up to 12 slowing the exp up to that point. also i made great muny off of selling df belts for 3-5pp until i found out that i could turn them in for mad exp. at 12 i stopped the orcs and went to explore nro. derv camps r what u should do there but be careful if u r at derv 1 b/c dorn is a badass that is a challenge to lvl 20's. it IS possible though to stay in ec and hunt giant spiders, darkweed snakes, young kodiaks and what not till 14. thats when everything there became green to me. and remember we R the best soloists b/c of our pets. at 14 u can hang around dervs for a while but i always had truble getting into a group. at this lvl i heded out to oasis but it is kinda dangerous there. try to get into an orc valley group b/c that gave me good exp up to me lvl (16) and i might hunt somemore. caimans r also a good lvl 14 thing to fight. i have ben doing alot of reserch and some peeple say at 16 u should hunt DW caimans. but alot more say u should either go out to Lake Rathetear or EK and hunt at some barbarian village. i have yet to discover what works best though. just remember that u rilly shouldnt pay for gg's or tp's anymore u should save up for INT increasing items. with our invis spell and our lvl being at 16 we should b able to travel through highpass ezily. if u r heding from ek to highpass there is a gaurd neer the ek bridge that escorts peeple through there(havent tried it yet though and he only leeves at certain times.) be more careful in ek though b/c there r higher lvl things 